      {
        "id": 280907,
        "name": null,
        "username": "FinnTimm",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/dbc845/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-09T20:24:52.894Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When you maximize an image or a video in a conversation, you can switch between them by swiping horizontally or close the maximized view (go back to the conversation) with a swipe down.</p>\n<p>But this doesn’t work when you write a message and maximize your media for previewing it. For closing the preview you have to tap the closing-x and cannot swipe down. And you also cannot swipe to the previous / next preview. You have to close the previewed image / video and then maximize another one.</p>\n<p>Solution: when you compose a message and maximize media for previewing it, it should be possible to swipe horizontally to switch between previews. And a swipe down should close the maximized preview and go back to the media-overview (of course the closing-x should still be available for users who don’t know the gesture).</p>\n<p>That would be much easier and much more comfortable to use.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2025-12-09T20:24:52.894Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
