        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/d9b06d/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-10T09:54:10.968Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"FinnTimm\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"73484\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/dbc845/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> FinnTimm:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>And a swipe down should close the maximized preview and go back to the media-overview (of course the closing-x should still be available for users who don’t know the gesture).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>To be consistent with the chat-view, in compose-view not only a swipe-down should close the maximized preview and go back to the media-overview, but also a swipe-up.</p>\n<p>(And I also agree, that swiping left and right should switch between the maximized previews.)</p>\n<p>That would improve usability and ease-of-use very much.</p>",
